[2] China (Xinjiang, Liaoning)
Date: Thu 30 Jul 2020
Source: Financial Times [abridged, edited]
https://www.ft.com/content/03f27af6-23c6-3d3c-8d65-849d500dcf2d


China has reported 112 new COVID-19 cases in the western region of Xinjiang, taking the total over the past 2 weeks to more than 500. The number of new COVID-19 cases in Xinjiang, which is home to the Uighur minority, has climbed sharply in recent days, despite efforts to limit the spread of the virus in the capital Urumqi.

More than 2 million people have been tested for the virus. Officials said Urumqi had a comparatively high number of people who tested positive for the virus but showed no symptoms. Asymptomatic cases are not included in China's official tally. The region's health authority said it had found a total of 108 asymptomatic cases as of Thursday [30 Jul 2020].

China reported a total of 123 local infections nationwide on Thursday [30 Jul 2020], the highest number since early March [2020].

An outbreak in Dalian, a port city in the northern province of Liaoning, grew by 11 infections to reach 69 cases over the past week. Almost 4.1 million samples from Dalian residents have been collected for coronavirus testing, state media reported early on Friday [31 Jul 2020]. A 2nd round of testing will be launched in high-risk districts. An additional 4 imported cases took China's overall number of COVID-19 cases to 84 292.

[Byline: Alice Woodhouse]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[During the period 16 Jul 2020 to 30 Jul 2020, there have been a total of 537 confirmed cases (not counting asymptomatic infections) associated with the outbreak in Xinjiang, the largest outbreak recorded by mainland China since mid-March 2020. The origin of this outbreak has not been defined to the best of my knowledge.

As for the outbreak in Liaoning province, during the period 22-30 Jul 2020, there have been a total of 74 cases associated with the outbreak in Dalian. This outbreak has had cases in Jilin, and Beijing. The outbreak seemed to be associated with a fish processing plant in Dalian and a nearby seafood market. Reminiscent of the seafood market in Wuhan and the seafood market in Beijing. Results of genomic testing of positive samples found in the market and in cases are still awaited.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://sacu.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/provmap.png and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7630702,155. - Mod.MPP]

